Topics covered in the course, such as basic concepts of entrepreneurship, different forms of entrepreneurship, value proposition, service / product development, marketing, sales, accounting, teamwork, business plan, business creation opportunities and stages in Estonia, enable physiotherapists to create a healthcare business. The subject course is strongly related to career planning - an entrepreneurial, active, determined, determined and ambitious student of physiotherapy will establish a company related with physiotherapy in the future.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to handle the basics of entrepreneurship and management in health services and its practical application.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Passing through the course the student know the basic of entrepreneurship forms, student able to compile simple business plan in area of health services, student can describe the basic principles of management, student demonstrate the team working.
